  "author_association": "MEMBER",
  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "The dispatcher parses the ABI signature and jumps to the specific tags, then the methods use `calldataload` again to load the specific arguments.  Would it make sense checking for the length of the supplied data with `calldatasize` that it meets the minimum required? Maybe when an optional keyword is used on the contract, like `safe`:\n\n```\nsafe contract Test {\n}\n```\n\nIn the case of fixed-length types that is a constant number. In the case of dynamic arguments, that would be the minimum length it would take.\n",
