    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Please explain how this is a security problem. The ABI is defined with the assumption that trailing zeros are ignored or can be omitted. This creates a \"malleability\" risk when using `msg.data`. On the other hard, `msg.data` provides low-level access and we also have this malleability risk when using non-32-byte-types.\n",
